SIP is structured as a layered protocol,
List of layers:
-   Syntax and Encoding Layer
-   Transport Layer
    -   Defines how a client sends requests and receives responses 
        and how a server receives requests and sends responses
-   Transaction Layer
    -   A transaction is a request sent by a client transaction to a server transaction, 
        along with all responses to that request.
    -   The transaction layer handles   application-layer retransmissions, 
        matching of responses to requests, and application-layer timeouts.
-   Transaction User Layer (User of Transaction)
    -   SIP entities are transaction user, that are:
            - User agent clients: construction of a request
            - User agent servers: processing of a request and generating a response
            - Stateful proxies: handles a REGISTER
            - Registrars